      • synthesize

        public static VectorType synthesize​(ScalarType elemType,
                                    int dimension)
        A pseudo-constructor for creating a VectorType which is not written out in the source code and whose dimension was computed by the compiler. When a source expression is available, use the regular constructor and (in contextual analysis) use setDimension() to supply the result of evaluating that expression.
        Parameters:
        elemType - The element type.
        dimension - The compiler-evaluated vector dimension.
        Returns:
        A vector type with the given element type and dimension.
